HEADWORD: Subdichotomy
<hw>Sub`di*chot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
subordinate, or inferior, division into parts; a subdivision.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many <qex>subdichatomies</qex> of petty schisms.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subdilated</ent>⟦br⟧
